  h2='Chickens/Ducks'
  p Growing up, I said pretty often I wanted to be a farmer. The main resoning? I could have chickens and ducks to hug. Being older, I understand that maybe hugging them isn't the best course of action, but I would still love to own my own. For a few months my dad and I kept chickens in the backyard for my cousin who was in the process of moving and I loved every second of it. Sadly when they left my mom said we couldn't get our own. I think she'd kill me if I came home one day with a handful of chickens. I do get to help our family friend Bob with his ducks whenever I visit. He dug his own duck pond and whenever he goes outside honking you see a line of ducks running towards him in the distance. I'm still working on perfecting my honk.
